.TH "drm_mode_addfb" 9 "drm_mode_addfb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_addfb \- add an FB to the graphics configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_addfb
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_mode_fb_cmd *or "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
drm device for the ioctl
.IP "or" 12
pointer to request structure
.IP "file_priv" 12
drm file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add a new FB to the specified CRTC, given a user request. This is the
original addfb ioctl which only supported RGB formats.

Called by the user via ioctl, or by an in-kernel client.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative errno on failure.
